INSERT INTO event VALUES (177, 801, 'SIL-West: Nexus', 'SIL-West', 'Nexus', 'Stephen Balzac an Aimee Yermish', NULL, NULL, 1, 'Nexus\r\n\r\nBenCon has been running successfully for a number of years.  Each year, more and more fans show up, and the costumes get better and better.  Guests get more distinguished, and the activities become steadily more interesting.  This year looks to be the best BenCon ever!   But...\r\n\r\nSomething Strange Is Going On...\r\n\r\nWhy are so many prominent scientists and military officials showing up?  And the costumes!  Those tentacles look incredibly realistic.  And why would anyone go to such lengths to produce such awful smelling slime?  Just what has happened to the weapons policy anyway?  Some of those toy guns look awfully frightening.  And just how do those guys get that little black box to float six inches off the ground?  What about the legendary ghost of the Sheraton?  Just another clever effect?  Why would anyone come to a science fiction convention dressed as a gangster?  What about that guy with the floppy hat and long scarf?   Nah, couldn\'t be.\r\n\r\nWelcome to Nexus, a real-time, real-space roleplaying game set at this year\'s BenCon.  Originally written in 1983 as Rekon-1 by Rick Dutton, Walt Freitag, Mike Massimilla, and Mike Munson, it is newly revised and expanded by Stephen Balzac and Aimee Yermish of the Society for Interactive Literature West.  Nexus will be running from Friday night May 28th until Sunday afternoon May 30th at BenCon \'99.  \r\n\r\nPlayers will take on the roles of scientists, criminals, government agents, aliens, aliens, and more aliens, each with their own background, history, goals, and desires.  Players in Nexus will, of course, be able to attend regular BenCon events without fear of losing their place in the game (and don\'t forget, BenCon extends through Monday this year as well, after completion of our game on Sunday afternoon).  But the world doesn\'t stop when you step out to the Hucksters\' Room...\r\n\r\nYour gamesmasters this year will be Carol Arko, Janice Gott, Richard Delgado, Amber O\'Toole, and Bradon Ebers.  To get in on the game, simply fill out the questionnaire on the next page (please print neatly, or request an electronic copy via e-mail) and send it directly to Carol Arko (13825 W. 6th Place, Golden, CO  80401 or ladybug@alum.mit.edu) so that we can cast you as something you\'ll have fun with!  Your checks, of course, should go directly to the RMBGA, as shown in the preregistration booklet, and we will not cast you until we receive confirmation of your paid preregistration…  The first round of casting will take place 2 weeks before the convention, so make sure you\'re signed up, paid, and have us a questionnaire by then if you want the best selection of characters!\r\n\r\nThe cost of the game will be $20 if you preregister for Nexus only, or it will be a $10 event if you choose to participate in other events at the con.  Make checks out to Rocky Mountain Benefit Gamer\'s Association (RMBGA).  Space is limited to 70 players, on a first-come, first-served basis.  All players in Nexus must be registered members of BenCon.\r\n\r\n Nexus Signup Sheet (mailto: Carol Arko, ladybug@alum.mit.edu or 13825 W. 6th Place, Golden, CO 80401)\r\n\r\nName: 				Phone: 				Age:		Gender:  M   F\r\nAddress: \r\nCity/State/Zip: \r\nE-mail address:				\r\nCan we send casting information to this e-mail address? \r\nIf so, can you receive attachments in Word \'97 format?\r\n\r\nWhat previous roleplaying experience have you had?  Briefly describe your favourite character and tell us why.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nHow much time do you plan to put into the game?\r\n          a) Play occasionally.\r\n          b) Have a few other things to do, but will spend a reasonable amount of time playing.\r\n          c) Will play most of the time, but I expect to eat and sleep.\r\n          d) The Vow:  No food, no sleep, only THE GAME!\r\n\r\nWho is your favourite SF character?  Which Doctor Who do you like best?  Do you prefer the new Star Trek or Trek Classic?  Which type of alien monster would you select to destroy Earth?\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nDo you want to be a Terran, or would you like to be an alien?  Please list any distinguishing characteristics which would suit you in this part.  Include tentacles, multiple heads, slime, a facility in Klingonese, etc.\r\n\r\n\r\nWhich of the following interest you?  \r\npolitics			characterization		  insidious scheming		widget-hunting\r\ncostuming		lounging around		  accomplishing goals		free-wheeling chaos\r\npublic speaking		back-alley sneaking	  information exchange	\r\n\r\nDo you have any special skills, hobbies, or interests which might aid us in casting?  Any that might not?  Are you good with a light-saber?\r\n\r\n\r\nPlease list six adjectives describing yourself, and six other adjectives describing the character you would like to play.\r\nYou:						Your Character:\r\n\r\n\r\nIs there anyone you would like to be teamed with?  No guarantees, but it does help if the other person(s) ask(s) to work with you, too.\r\n\r\nAre there any slots in which you know you are doing other con activity(ies)?  Please note that you should be available during the Sunday afternoon slot (12:30 - 4:30 p.m.), as the game tends to climax then.\r\n\r\n\r\nWhat else should we know about you that we didn\'t think to ask?', '8', 'Beginner-Rules Taught', NULL, 805, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, 20020714202833);
